The paper focuses on developing an interactive visualization technique to help users understand and validate predictive models, which involves both human-computer interaction (HCI) and artificial intelligence (AI) aspects. Therefore, cs.HC is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with machine learning models, which falls under cs.AI and cs.LG. The paper discusses the extraction of knowledge representation from the black-box model, which is related to information retrieval (IR) and semantic web (SI), making them likely sub-categories as well.
